3. ETHICAL STANDARDS:

This section lists conditions the licensee must comply with in order to have rights under this license.

The rights granted to You by this License are expressly made subject to Your compliance with the following ethical standards:

A. You must not use the Work for or in connection with:

i. Violations of human rights, as defined by the United Nations Universal Declaration of Human Rights (https://www.un.org/en/universal-declaration-human-rights/), civil rights, civil liberties, labor rights, privacy rights, or immigrants' rights;

ii. Deliberate discrimination, including but not limited to on the basis of age, disability, gender identity, nationality, race, religion, sexual orientation, or any other legally protected category or class;

iii. Law enforcement or military activities;

iv. Lying, deception, defamation, harassment, stalking, or any other forms of harm targeted towards any person, group of people, or organization;

v. Environmental destruction, including but not limited to actions directly or indirectly supporting or profiting from:

1. Deforestation or other actions that destroy habitats or contribute to species extinction

2. Pollution that harms any living thing

3. The burning of fossil fuels and industries that emit dangerous levels of greenhouse gasses into the atmosphere 

4. Mining that pollutes the environment or harms ecosystems

5. Any other ecologically destructive activities;

vi. Automated decision-making that adversely affects an individual's rights;

vii. The analysis of production, development, and distribution of weapons, surveillance tools or any other technology meant to harm, spy on, or control people.

B. You must not use the Work in any capacity to support, promote, participate in, or profit from:

i. The Israeli occupation of Palestine in violation of international law

ii. Israeli settlements in occupied Palestine in violation of international law

iii. The Israeli system of apartheid

iv. The actions of the Israeli military, including but not limited to the Israeli Defense Forces.

C. You must not use the Work if You are employed by, work for, or operate on behalf of law enforcement, military, or surveillance organizations/institutions.

D. You must not use the Work to engage in fossil fuel production, distribution, or consumption.

E. You must not use the Work if Your commercial operations involve fossil fuel development, distribution, or consumption.

